<H2>Package Menu</H2>
<P>The package menu gives options for manipulating the currently selected package</P>
<P>This menu is a sub menu shown from the menu for the main window</P>
<P>It provide the following options
<UL>
<LI>Install - install or upgrade the selected package.
    When selected it leads to the <A HREF="configpackage.htm">Configure Package Window</A> to install/upgrade the package.
    This option is disabled if the package is installed and up to date.
</LI>
<LI>Remove - remove the selected application.
    When selected it leads to the <A HREF="configpackage.htm">Configure Package Window</A> to remove the package.
    This option is disabled if the package is not installed.
</LI>
<LI>Components - shows the <A HREF="apps.htm">Components Window</A>
    which shows the components installed by this package and allows them to be linked to and copied.
    It is disabled if the package is not installed.
</LI>
<LI>Info - shows the <A HREF="info.htm">Information window</A> that gives more information on
    the package.
</LI>
<LI>Copyright - shows the copyright information for the package.
    It is disabled if the package is not installed.
</LI>
<LI>Installed files - shows the list of files that have been installed for this package (excluding package control files).
    It is disabled if the package is not installed.
</LI>
</UL>
</P>

</BODY>
